Live broadcast date: Thursday, 17 September 2020 09h00 New York | 13h00 GMT | 14h00 London | 15h00 Paris | 15h00 Amsterdam | 15h00 Johannesburg | 18h30 New Delhi | 21h00 Singapore | 23h00 Melbourne The concept of international best practice represents a global consensus among representatives of government, industry and international development partners as to what constitutes appropriate ground rules and protections for the achievement of the objectives of the industry and the public goals of the government. While the Nigerian mining sector may be in its infancy, the government is looking to grow the sector and from the offset is looking to ensure the industry can be benchmarked against global best practices. Join Mining Review Africa and Nigeria Mining Week as we unpack this topic at length – covering all critical topics that must be considered to ensure the country’s mining sector is world-class. Dr Uchechukwu Ogah, Honourable Minister of State, Ministry of Mines and Steel Development, Nigeria Honourable Janet Adeyemi, Women in Mining Rukaiya El-Rufia, Head: Sustainability, PwC, Nigeria